00:50:05.408 --> 00:50:09.388
Census tracts have on average about 5,000 residents, compared to 20,000

842
00:50:09.448 --> 00:50:12.758
in a ZIP code. So you prefer to work with that smaller level

843
00:50:12.868 --> 00:50:15.228
geography when you're working with the exposure data.

844
00:50:16.388 --> 00:50:20.148
So you can link these existing data sources

845
00:50:20.228 --> 00:50:24.008
to individual level data from EMRs, electronic

