00:53:48.038 --> 00:53:50.368
cohort that showed that

904
00:53:51.548 --> 00:53:53.057
psychosocial stressors,

905
00:53:54.268 --> 00:53:57.968
anxiety, depression, mental health, is associated with

906
00:53:58.008 --> 00:54:01.058
shorter telomere length under a chronic stress hypothesis.

907
00:54:01.728 --> 00:54:05.448
And we wanted to expand that to see

908
00:54:05.568 --> 00:54:09.268
if, under a chronic stress hypothesis, these macro level

909
00:54:09.368 --> 00:54:12.398
factors, these SSDOH factors, could

910
00:54:12.508 --> 00:54:16.258
also be implicated or associated with

911
00:54:16.288 --> 00:54:19.728
telomere length. And what we found, we

912
00:54:19.848 --> 00:54:23.328
had access to some of these environmental measures.

913
00:54:23.368 --> 00:54:27.128
Even when we adjust for those individual level factors like perceived

914
00:54:27.228 --> 00:54:31.168
stress and depression, that these macro factors,

